loadMacros(
  "PGstandard.pl",
  "PGchoicemacros.pl",
  "PGcourse.pl"
);



install_problem_grader(~~&std_problem_grader);
TEXT(beginproblem());

$showPartialCorrectAnswers = 0;





# output the text of the problem



$b = random(2,40,1);

$c = random(2,40,1);



TEXT(EV2(<<EOT));



Consider the inequality : \( | x - $b | \le $c \)



The solution of this inequality consists of one or more of the
intervals \( (-\infty, A] \), \( [A,B] \) and \( [B,\infty) \) where 
\( A < B \).

$PAR

Find \( A \) \{ ans_rule(10) \}

$PAR

Find \( B \) \{ ans_rule(10) \}

$PAR

For each interval, answer YES or NO to whether the interval is included in 
the solution.

$PAR

\( (-\infty, A] \) \{ ans_rule(10) \}

$PAR

\( [A,B] \) \{ ans_rule(10) \}

$PAR

\( [B,\infty) \) \{ ans_rule(10) \}

EOT





$ans1 = -$c+$b; 

$ans2 = $c+$b; 

$ans3 = "no";

$ans4 = "yes";

$ans5 = "no";



ANS(num_cmp($ans1));

ANS(num_cmp($ans2));

ANS(str_cmp($ans3));

ANS(str_cmp($ans4));

ANS(str_cmp($ans5));



